findings.title: if / else stackheightmismatchhoneypot
findings.description: A vulnerability exists where an if/else branch with different resulting stack heights can lead to stack manipulation, allowing an attacker to drain the contract by repeatedly calling the withdraw function.

findings.title: List literals can have mismatched types due to an off-by-one error
findings.description: Inconsistent type checking for list literals due to an off-by-one error, allowing lists with mismatched types.
